Metropolitan Avenue, north side, between 79th Street and 79th Place. From left to right are the following shops: Bauman, a shoemaker at No. 2243; Henry Reitenback, a blacksmith at 2245; Hirsch's feed store at 2247, and Nos. 2249-2253 at the right (flat roofs) owned by Hirsch-Philip and Joseph Hirsch owned all homes in this view in 1924.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
